</div><div class="BVRRReviewTitleContainer"><span class="BVRRLabel BVRRReviewTitlePrefix"></span><span property="v:summary" class="BVRRValue BVRRReviewTitle">LG OLED 65" C5</span><span class="BVRRLabel BVRRReviewTitleSuffix"></span></div><div class="BVRRReviewDateContainer"><span class="BVRRLabel BVRRReviewDatePrefix">on&nbsp;</span><span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2025-10-22" class="BVRRValue BVRRReviewDate">October 22, 2025<span property="v:value-title"></span></span><span class="BVRRLabel BVRRReviewDateSuffix"></span></div></div>
<div class="BVRRReviewDisplayStyle5BodyUser"><div class="BVRRUserNicknameContainer"><span class="BVRRLabel BVRRUserNicknamePrefix">Posted by:&nbsp;</span><span class="BVRRValue BVRRUserNickname"><span property="v:reviewer" class="BVRRNickname">DJT1 </span></span><span class="BVRRLabel BVRRUserNicknameSuffix"></span></div><div class="BVRRContextDataContainer"></div></div> <div class="BVRRReviewDisplayStyle5BodyContent"><div class="BVRRReviewDisplayStyle5BodyContentPrimary"><div class="BVRRReviewDisplayStyle5Text"> <div class="BVRRReviewTextContainer">
<div class="BVRRReviewTextParagraph BVRRReviewTextFirstParagraph BVRRReviewTextLastParagraph"> <span class="BVRRReviewText">Upgrade from my 65" OLED C9. My 4th LG OLED going back to a much earlier curved screen and no regrets with my purchase of any one of them. With modern OLED TVs, the quality is so good the improvements become miniscule from yr to yr, but even so and as good as my 65" C9 is, this is noticeably better in picture clarity. Most noticeably on upscaling on normal TV viewing, but not limited to just test. Just an overall better picture. With the deals available now i would highly recommend this unit.</span>
</div> </div>
</div><div class="BVRRReviewDisplayStyle5Tags"></div><div class="BVRRReviewDisplayStyle5Recommendations"></div></div><div class="BVRRReviewDisplayStyle5BodyContentSecondary"></div></div>
<div class="BVRRReviewDisplayStyle5Footer"></div> <div class="BVRRReviewDisplayStyle5BodyClient"><div class="BVRRReviewClientResponsesContainer"><div class="BVRRReviewClientResponseContainer"><div class="BVRRReviewClientResponseHeader"><span class="BVRRReviewClientResponseTitle">Response from lg.com</span><span class="BVRRReviewClientResponseSubtitle"><span class="BVRRReviewClientResponseSubtitlePrefix">By&nbsp;</span><span class="BVRRReviewClientResponseSubtitleName">^Rich</span><span class="BVRRReviewClientResponseSubtitleNameSuffix">,&nbsp;</span><span class="BVRRReviewClientResponseSubtitleDept">LG Digital Care Team</span><span class="BVRRReviewClientResponseSubtitleDeptSuffix">,&nbsp;</span><span class="BVRRReviewClientResponseSubtitleDate">December 6, 2025</span><span class="BVRRReviewClientResponseSubtitleDateSuffix"></span></span></div><div class="BVRRReviewClientResponseText">Hi DJ, thank you for sharing your experience with the LG OLED65C5PUA. It’s impressive to hear this is your fourth LG OLED and that each one has delivered quality you can count on. We’re glad the improved picture clarity and upscaling have stood out compared to your C9, making everyday viewing even better. Your recommendation highlights the value of this model, and we’re delighted it continues to meet your expectations. For any further assistance, feel free to DM us at @LGUSSupport.<br><br>#LifesGood ❤️ LG Digital Care Team ^Rich</div></div></div></div>
